.SH PlmIndex
Compute the index of an array corresponding to degree \f[CR]l\f[R] and
angular order \f[CR]m\f[R].
.SH Usage
\f[CR]index\f[R] = PlmIndex (\f[CR]l\f[R], \f[CR]m\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]index\f[R] : function output, integer(int32)
Index of an array of associated Legendre functions corresponding to
degree \f[CR]l\f[R] and angular order \f[CR]m\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
.TP
\f[CR]m\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The angular order.
.SH Description
\f[CR]PlmIndex\f[R] will calculate the index of an array of associated
Legendre functions corresponding to degree \f[CR]l\f[R] and angular
order \f[CR]m\f[R].
The input arrays are generated by routines such as \f[CR]PlmBar\f[R],
\f[CR]PlmBar_d1\f[R], \f[CR]PlmSchmidt\f[R], \f[CR]PlmSchmidt_d1\f[R],
\f[CR]PlmON\f[R], \f[CR]PlmON_d1\f[R], \f[CR]PLegendreA\f[R], and
\f[CR]PLegendreA_d1\f[R].
The array index is equal to \f[CR]l*(l+1)/2+m+1\f[R].
.SH See also
plmbar, plmbar_d1, plmschmidt, plmschmidt_d1, plmon, plmon_d1,
